    "body": "Hi\r\n\r\nOur users want an error message printed if \"spack load\" does not find a package installed.  We use environment modules which will print an error message if you try to load a module that does not exist.  For example if I forget the last character in a module that Spack installed:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nuser@server[~]$ module load git-2.12.1-gcc-6.3.0-vl5jrn\r\nModuleCmd_Load.c(213):ERROR:105: Unable to locate a modulefile for 'git-2.12.1-gcc-6.3.0-vl5jrn'\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nCould Spack simply print that error message or something similar?\r\n\r\n```\r\nuser@server[~]$ spack load blah\r\nuser@server[~]$ \r\n```\r\n\r\n",
